<div id="content">                                            
                                            <p><a href="../index.html" class="breadcrumb">Club Penguin Help</a> &gt; <a href="../technical_help.html" class="breadcrumb">Technical Help</a> &gt; Some parts of the game aren&rsquo;t appearing on my screen?</p>
                <h1>Some parts of the game aren&rsquo;t appearing on my screen? </h1>
              <p>There are two main reasons why this could be happening:</p>
              <ol>
                <li><strong>Reason 1 - Screen Resolution
                  </strong><br />
                  You might not have enough <strong><a href="glossary-technical-terms.htm#screen-res" >screen resolution</a></strong> to show these parts of the game. It&rsquo;s easy to  adjust your screen resolution.<br />
                  <br />
                  <ul>
                    <li><a href="#PC" >If you are using PC</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#MAC" >If you are using a Mac</a><br />
                      <br />
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li><a href="#download-flash-player" >Download a new flash player </a></li>
              </ol>
			  
              <p><a name="PC" id="PC"></a></p>
              <h2>Reason #1:              </h2>
              <div class="content-tall-left">
              		<p><strong>If you are using a PC</strong>:</p>
              		<ol>
                		<li>Log  out of Club Penguin. Go to the desktop of your computer.<br />
                 		 <br />
                		</li>
                		<li>Click  on the right button on your mouse. A box will pop up. Click on &ldquo;Properties.&rdquo;<br />
                  		<br />
                		</li>
                		<li>Another  box will pop up. Look at the tabs running across the top. Click on &ldquo;Settings.&rdquo;<br />
                  		<br />
                		</li>
                		<li>You  will see a little box titled &ldquo;Screen Resolution.&rdquo; In this box is a bar with an  arrow on it. Use your mouse to drag the bar to the right until the screen  resolution reads 1024 by 768 pixels or higher.<br />
                  		<br />
						</li>
                		<li>Click  &ldquo;OK.&rdquo;<br />
                  		<br />
                		</li>
                		<li>Log  back on to Club Penguin and try playing the game again.</li>
                    </ol>
              </div>
              <div class="content-right">
              		<img src="images/Screen-ResWin-step1.gif" width="350" height="220" /><br />
                    <img src="images/Screen-ResWin-step2.gif" width="350" height="220" />
              </div>
              <div align="right">
              		<a href="#top" class="breadcrumb">back to top</a>	
              </div>
            
            
            <p>&nbsp;</p> 
			<div class="content-tall-left">
            		<a name="MAC" id="MAC"></a><p><strong>If you are using a Mac</strong>:</p>
              <ol>
                <li>Log  out of Club Penguin.<br />
                  <br />
                </li>
                <li>Click  on the blue apple icon on the top left of your screen. A menu will appear.  Click on &ldquo;System Preferences.&rdquo;<br />
                  <br />
                </li>
                <li>Find  the icon that looks like a computer monitor. It will say &ldquo;Display&rdquo; underneath.  Click on this icon.<br />
                  <br />
                </li>
                <li>A  box will pop up. Inside this box you will see the word &ldquo;Resolutions.&rdquo; Make sure  that the resolution highlighted is &ldquo;1024 x 768&rdquo; or higher. If it is not, use  your mouse to highlight &ldquo;1024 x 768.&rdquo;<br />
                  <br />
                </li>
                <li>Click  on the red button on the top of the box to close the box.<br />  
                  <br />
                </li>
                <li>
                  Log  back on to Club Penguin and try playing the game again.                </li>
              </ol>
            </div>
            <div class="content-right">
            		<img src="images/Screen-ResMac-step1.gif" width="350" height="220" /><br />
                    <img src="images/Screen-ResMac-step2.gif" width="350" height="220" />
            </div>				  
			<div align="right">
              		<a href="#top" class="breadcrumb">back to top</a>	
            </div>
			  
			  
 
			  <a name="download-flash-player" id="download-flash-player"></a><h2>Reason #2:</h2>
              <p>You might not have the right version of Adobe Flash  Player to run the game properly.&nbsp; You  will need to download a new <a href="glossary-technical-terms.htm#flash-player" >flash  player</a>. There are a few ways to do this;</p>
              <ol>
                <li>Try  to play a game on Club Penguin. You may get a message that says you need to  download the newest version of Flash Player. Don&rsquo;t ignore it. Click &ldquo;OK&rdquo; to  start and follow the steps you are given.<br />
                  <br />
				</li>
                <li>Visit <a href="http://www.macromedia.com/go/getflashplayer/" target="_blank" >Flash Player Download Center</a> to  update Flash Player.  Follow the instructions on the Adobe website.</li>
              </ol>
              <p align="right"><a href="#top" class="breadcrumb">back to top</a> </p>
              
</div>              
